Prerequisites
-------------
Java 1.6 or later
Maven (tested on v 3.0.2)

Build User API from Source
---------------------------------
* Unzip/untar the source file or check out from git
* cd to project folder and type
	$ mvn clean install
	Note: in order to skip tests use the command
			$ mvn clean install -Dmaven.test.skip=true
* Alternatively, all  compressed binary distributions can be found at <PROJECT DIR>/target/

Running Tests
-------------
* Unit tests & integrations tests will run while Apache Airavata User API is built from source (without "-Dmaven.test.skip=true").


Installing the Airavata User API Server
------------------------------
No installation is necessary. Just extract the compressed distribution.

Starting Apache Airavata User API Server
-------------------------------
* extract airavata-userapi.bin.zip and navigate to <AIRAVATA_USER_API_HOME>/bin
* type for following command to start the Airavata User API Server
	MAC/Unix systems
		$ ./userapi-server.sh
	Note: Pass "-h" as parameters to see more options when starting the server
